oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Muncy Store
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: T. O. Muncy's store on Highway 75 in Leoni, seven miles out toward McMinnville.
Open from 1920-1960. Muncy was a major buyer of baskets and chairs from local basket makers. Tully Oscar Muncy (1877-1960)
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Interiors; Stores & shops; Merchants
